1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,169
For about 15 years, I've been close to a fellow I'll call Bob W. Bob is in his late 50s.

2
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:08,929
He came up the hard way.

3
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:15,489
With a hit-or-miss education and no money, Bob found himself out of work in 1931.

4
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:17,649
But he's always been a scrambler.

5
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:22,610
Not one to be idle, Bob started an upholstery shop in his garage.

6
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:31,729
Thanks to his untiring efforts, the business grew, and today it's a modern furniture manufacturing plant with over 300 employees.

7
00:00:32,320 --> 00:00:34,689
Today, Bob is a millionaire.

8
00:00:34,960 --> 00:00:38,530
Money and material things have ceased to be a concern.

9
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:41,249
But Bob is rich in other ways, too.

10
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:45,650
He's a millionaire in friends, contentment, and satisfaction.

11
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:52,209
Of Bob's many fine qualities, his tremendous desire to help other people stands out.

12
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:59,090
Bob is human, and he's a specialist in treating others the way human beings want to be treated.

13
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:04,209
One day, Bob and I were discussing the matter of criticizing people.

14
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:08,130
Bob's human way of doing it is a master formula.

15
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:09,810
Here's the way he put it.

16
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:15,010
I don't think you could find anybody who would say I'm a softie or a weakling.

17
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:16,209
I run a business.

18
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:19,169
When something isn't going right, I fix it.

19
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:22,290
But it's the way I fix it that's important.

20
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:32,449
If employees are doing something wrong or are making a mistake, I am doubly careful not to hurt their feelings and make them feel small or embarrassed.

21
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:35,249
I just use four simple steps.

22
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:38,050
First, I talk to them privately.

23
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:41,729
Second, I praise them for what they are doing well.

24
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:48,370
Third, I point out the one thing at the moment that they could do better and I help them find the way.

25
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:52,130
Fourth, I praise them again on their good points.

26
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:55,010
And this four-step formula works.

27
00:01:55,199 --> 00:02:00,850
When I do it this way, people thank me because I've found that's exactly the way they like it.

28
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:06,050
When they walk out of this office, they have been reminded that they are not only pretty good,

29
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,890
they can be even better.

30
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:14,370
I've been betting on people all my life, Bob says, and the better I treat them,

31
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:16,530
the more good things happen to me.

32
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:18,929
I honestly don't plan it that way.

33
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,169
That's just the way it works out.

34
00:02:21,679 --> 00:02:23,330
Let me give you an example.

35
00:02:23,439 --> 00:02:29,090
Back about, oh, five or six years ago, one of the production men came to work drunk.

36
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:32,050
Pretty soon there was a commotion in the plant.

37
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:38,130
It seems this fellow had taken a five-gallon can of lacquer and was splashing it all over the place.

38
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:44,610
Well, the other workmen took the lacquer away from him, and the plant superintendent escorted him out.

39
00:02:45,439 --> 00:02:50,050
I walked outside and found him sitting against the building in a kind of stupor.

40
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:53,890
I helped him up, put him in my car and took him to his home.

41
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,650
His wife was frantic.

42
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:59,169
I tried to reassure her that everything would be all right.

43
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:01,410
Oh, but you don't understand, she said.
